{"title_page": "The Flavor of Corn", "text_new": "{{Cleanup|reason=does not meet standard encyclopaedic style|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Flavor of Corn\n| image          = File:Il Sapore Del Grano kiss.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| border         = \n| alt            = 12-year-old Duilio steals a chaste kiss from his handsome young teacher Lorenzo.\n| caption        = \n| film name      = '''''Il sapore del grano'''''\n| director       = [[imdbname:0196016|Gianni Da Campo]]\n| producer       = Chantal Lenoble-Bergamo<br>Enzo Porcelli\n| writer         = Gianni Da Campo\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} -->\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = [[imdbname:0501660|Lorenzo Lena]]<br>[[imdbname:0582342|Marco Mestriner]]\n| music          = [[Franco Piersanti]]\n| cinematography = Emilio Bestetti\n| editing        = \n| studio         = Antea Films & [[RAI]]\n| distributor    = SACIS (Italy)<br>Award Films (U.S.)\n| released       = <!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} -->1986\n| runtime        = 93 minutes\n| country        = [[Italy]]\n| language       = Italian\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n \n'''''The Flavor of Corn''''' ({{lang-it|'''Il sapore del grano'''}}; also known in English as '''''The Taste of Wheat''''') is a 1986 [[Cinema of Italy|Italian]] [[coming-of-age film]]. Written and directed by [[imdbname:0196016|Gianni Da Campo]], the film stars [[imdbname:0501660|Lorenzo Lena]] and [[imdbname:0582342|Marco Mestriner]] and follows the story of a [[homosexuality|same-sex romance]] that develops between a young professor and his 12-year-old student.<ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite web|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/121057/Sapore-del-Grano/overview|title=Sapore del Grano (1986)|author=|accessdate=May 4, 2013|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref name=\"CulturaGay.it\">{{cite web|url=http://www.culturagay.it/cg/recensione.php?id=11024|title=Il sapore del grano (Italian)|author=|date=August 5, 2008|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=CulturaGay.it}}</ref><ref name=\"Queer.de\">{{cite web|url=http://www.queer.de/detail.php?article_id=13357|title=Sch\u00fcler liebt Lehrer (German)|author=|date=December 17, 2010|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=Queer.de}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLorenzo is a young man, a newly qualified teacher on his first posting, who has been appointed to a small Italian village. One of his  pupils, a cute and smart 12-year-old boy named Duilio, a farmer's son, gradually grows to love Lorenzo and they become good friends but the boy wishes Lorenzo was his older brother. Lorenzo often visits Duilio's  home, meets his family, and they become good friends. Lorenzo meanwhile meets a young woman, with whom he falls in love. However, the relationship with his girlfriend is not perfect and he chooses to break up with her as she is about to be married. She and her fianc\u00e9 agree to have an open relationship but Lorenzo declines the offer. Meanwhile, Lorenzo becomes much closer to Duilio and they often spend time with each other.  The boy is given books and other things and the boy in turn makes and gives his friend a carved boat and poems.  The boy kisses his teacher in a farm building on the lips. The boy's sister returns and all three become friends. But many things change after Duilio's stepmother begins to distrust Lorenzo and says as much to his father. Gradually, at the request of the boy's father who knows that his son loves his teacher more than his father, they meet less often. Duilio has to work on his father's farm in the afternoon, but Duilio still needs Lorenzo and misses him. To get out of this difficult situation, Lorenzo decides to leave the village and Duilio forever.  His mother realises that the teacher's feelings for the boy are pure and asks to be forgiven. His family says he is always welcome anytime.  The boy knows his teacher will never return not that he can not return.  The teacher rejects the idea of a loving but homosexual relationship with the boy and has to leave.  The boy does not know why his friend will never come back and runs after the taxi.  The teachers weeps at the lost love with a boy who tells him everything and trusts him totally.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[imdbname:0501660|Lorenzo Lena]] as Lorenzo\n* [[imdbname:0582342|Marco Mestriner]] as Duilio\n* Alba Mottura as Cecilia\n* Egidio Termine as Bruno\n* Mattia Pinoli as Grandpa\n* Paolo Garlato as Father\n* Elena Barbalich as Adalgisa\n* Elisabetta Barbini as Grandma\n* [[Marina Vlady]] as Stepmother\n\n==Reception==\nUpon its release in North America, the film received positive reviews for its sensitive portrayal of the romantic relationship that develops between a first year school teacher and his adolescent admirer.  [[Allrovi]] commended the film's handling of its delicate subject matter writing, \"This drama addresses with great care the awakening of homosexual desire in a 12-year-old boy.\"<ref name=\"Allrovi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allrovi.com/movies/movie/sapore-del-grano-v121057|title=Sapore Del Grano - Cast, Reviews, Summary, and Awards|author=|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=[[Allrovi|Allrovi.com]]}}</ref>  ''[[The Seattle Times]]'' lauded the film for being \"unflinchingly honest\" and the San Francisco ''[[Bay Area Reporter]]'' described the story as \"fascinating\", adding that the film \"approaches its forbidden topic with an even hand and a warm heart.\"<ref name=\"Award Films\">{{cite AV media |people= |year=1994|title=The Flavor of Corn|trans-title=|medium=VHS|url=https://www.amazon.com/The-Flavor-of-Corn/dp/B000HOJEMY|archiveurl= |archivedate= |format=|publisher=Award Films International |location=Los Angeles|isbn=1-884193-02-1}}</ref>  In September 2012, a \"special event\" screening of the film was arranged as part of a 1980s retrospective at the 17th Milano Film Festival, which touted the film as a \"hidden jewel\" that managed to avoid the familiar tropes and clich\u00e9s employed by other films of the genre.<ref name=\"FMM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festivalmixmilano.com/2012/il-sapore-del-grano/|title=Il sapore del grano (Italian)|author=|date=June 25, 2012|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=FestivalMixMilano.com}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=5; style=\"text-align: center; background:#ffffff;\"\n!Year !!Organization !!Award !!Recipient(s) !!Result\n|-\n| rowspan=2|1986||rowspan=2|[[:it:Laceno d'oro|Festival del cinema neorealistico]]<br>(Neorealist Film Festival)||[[:it:Franco Arcalli|Kim Arcalli]] Plaque||[[:it:Gianni Da Campo|Gianni Da Campo]]<br>(Director)||{{won}}\n|-\n| [[:it:Pietro Bianchi (critico cinematografico)|Pietro Bianchi]] Plaque ||Chantal Bergamo & Enzo Porcelli<br>(Producers)||{{won}}\n|}\n\n==Home media==\nSince its original release in 1986, the film has been subtitled in various languages and distributed internationally on VHS and DVD in numerous countries, including Italy (released as ''Il sapore del grano''),<ref name=\"FilmScoop.it\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmscoop.it/film_al_cinema/ilsaporedelgrano.asp|title=''Il sapore del grano''|author=|date=September 1986|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=(VHS). FilmScoop.it}}</ref><ref name=\"Amazon.it\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.it/Sapore-Del-Grano-Marina-Vlady/dp/B005Q6KYPY/|title=''Il Sapore Del Grano''|author=|date=November 16, 2011|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=(DVD). Amazon.it}}</ref> China (translated as ''The Taste of Wheat''),<ref name=\"MPDB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.movieposterdb.com/poster/01d61613|title=''The Taste of Wheat''|author=|date=September 7, 2011|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=(DVD). MoviePosterDB}}</ref> Germany (released as ''Die Qual der Liebe''),<ref name=\"Amazon.de\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Die-Qual-Liebe-Lorenzo-Lena/dp/B004BIP0P2|title=''Die Qual der Liebe''|author=|date=December 20, 2010|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=(DVD). Amazon.de}}</ref> and the United States (released as ''The Flavor of Corn'').<ref name=\"Award Films\"/>  In 1994, Award Films International released the film in North America in the VHS format with English subtitles.<ref name=\"Award Films\"/>  As of 2013, no evidence of an official North American DVD release has been found.  However, in November 2011, Ripley's Home Video released the film in Italy in the Region 2 DVD format, which includes the option to watch with English subtitles.<ref name=\"Amazon.it\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0102840}}\n*{{Allrovi title|id=121057}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Flavor of Corn, The}}\n[[Category:1986 films]]\n[[Category:Childhood LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Italian films]]\n[[Category:Italian LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Juvenile sexuality in films]]\n[[Category:Films about pederasty]]\n[[Category:Teen LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related coming-of-age films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup|reason=does not meet standard encyclopaedic style|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Flavor of Corn\n| image          = File:Il Sapore Del Grano kiss.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| border         = \n| alt            = 12-year-old Duilio steals a chaste kiss from his handsome young teacher Lorenzo.\n| caption        = \n| film name      = '''''Il sapore del grano'''''\n| director       = [[imdbname:0196016|Gianni Da Campo]]\n| producer       = Chantal Lenoble-Bergamo<br>Enzo Porcelli\n| writer         = Gianni Da Campo\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} -->\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = [[imdbname:0501660|Lorenzo Lena]]<br>[[imdbname:0582342|Marco Mestriner]]\n| music          = [[Franco Piersanti]]\n| cinematography = Emilio Bestetti\n| editing        = \n| studio         = Antea Films & [[RAI]]\n| distributor    = SACIS (Italy)<br>Award Films (U.S.)\n| released       = <!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} -->1986\n| runtime        = 93 minutes\n| country        = [[Italy]]\n| language       = Italian\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n \n'''''The Flavor of Corn''''' ({{lang-it|'''Il sapore del grano'''}}; also known in English as '''''The Taste of Wheat''''') is a 1986 [[Cinema of Italy|Italian]] [[coming-of-age film]]. Written and directed by [[imdbname:0196016|Gianni Da Campo]], the film stars [[imdbname:0501660|Lorenzo Lena]] and [[imdbname:0582342|Marco Mestriner]] and follows the story of a [[homosexuality|same-sex romance]] that develops between a young professor and his 12-year-old student.<ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite web|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/121057/Sapore-del-Grano/overview|title=Sapore del Grano (1986)|author=|accessdate=May 4, 2013|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref name=\"CulturaGay.it\">{{cite web|url=http://www.culturagay.it/cg/recensione.php?id=11024|title=Il sapore del grano (Italian)|author=|date=August 5, 2008|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=CulturaGay.it}}</ref><ref name=\"Queer.de\">{{cite web|url=http://www.queer.de/detail.php?article_id=13357|title=Sch\u00fcler liebt Lehrer (German)|author=|date=December 17, 2010|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=Queer.de}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLorenzo is a young man, a newly qualified teacher on his first posting, who has been appointed to a small Italian village. One of his  pupils, a cute and smart 12-year-old boy named Duilio, a farmer's son, gradually grows to love Lorenzo and they become good friends but the boy wishes Lorenzo was his older brother. Lorenzo often visits Duilio's  home, meets his family, and they become good friends. Lorenzo meanwhile meets a young woman, with whom he falls in love. However, the relationship with his girlfriend is not perfect and he chooses to break up with her as she is about to be married. She and her fiance agree to have an open relationship but Lorenzo declines the offer. Meanwhile Lorenzo becomes much closer to Duilio and they often spend time with each other.  The boy is given books and other things and the boy in turn makes and gives his friend a carved boat and poems.  The boy kisses his teacher in a farm building on the lips. The boy's sister returns and all three become friends. But many things change after Duilio's stepmother begins to distrust Lorenzo and says as much to his father. Gradually, at the request of the boy's father who knows that his son loves his teacher more than his father, they meet less often. Duilio has to work on his father's farm in the afternoon, but Duilio still needs Lorenzo and misses him. To get out of this difficult situation, Lorenzo decides to leave the village and Duilio forever.  His mother realises that the teacher's feelings for the boy are pure and asks to be forgiven. His family says he is always welcome anytime.  The boy knows his teacher will never return not that he can not return.  The teacher rejects the idea of a loving but homosexual relationship with the boy and has to leave.  The boy does not know why his friend will never come back and runs after the taxi.  The teachers weeps at the lost love with a boy who tells him everything and trusts him totally.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[imdbname:0501660|Lorenzo Lena]] as Lorenzo\n* [[imdbname:0582342|Marco Mestriner]] as Duilio\n* Alba Mottura as Cecilia\n* Egidio Termine as Bruno\n* Mattia Pinoli as Grandpa\n* Paolo Garlato as Father\n* Elena Barbalich as Adalgisa\n* Elisabetta Barbini as Grandma\n* [[Marina Vlady]] as Stepmother\n\n==Reception==\nUpon its release in North America, the film received positive reviews for its sensitive portrayal of the romantic relationship that develops between a first year school teacher and his adolescent admirer.  [[Allrovi]] commended the film's handling of its delicate subject matter writing, \"This drama addresses with great care the awakening of homosexual desire in a 12-year-old boy.\"<ref name=\"Allrovi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allrovi.com/movies/movie/sapore-del-grano-v121057|title=Sapore Del Grano - Cast, Reviews, Summary, and Awards|author=|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=[[Allrovi|Allrovi.com]]}}</ref>  ''[[The Seattle Times]]'' lauded the film for being \"unflinchingly honest\" and the San Francisco ''[[Bay Area Reporter]]'' described the story as \"fascinating\", adding that the film \"approaches its forbidden topic with an even hand and a warm heart.\"<ref name=\"Award Films\">{{cite AV media |people= |year=1994|title=The Flavor of Corn|trans-title=|medium=VHS|url=https://www.amazon.com/The-Flavor-of-Corn/dp/B000HOJEMY|archiveurl= |archivedate= |format=|publisher=Award Films International |location=Los Angeles|isbn=1-884193-02-1}}</ref>  In September 2012, a \"special event\" screening of the film was arranged as part of a 1980s retrospective at the 17th Milano Film Festival, which touted the film as a \"hidden jewel\" that managed to avoid the familiar tropes and clich\u00e9s employed by other films of the genre.<ref name=\"FMM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festivalmixmilano.com/2012/il-sapore-del-grano/|title=Il sapore del grano (Italian)|author=|date=June 25, 2012|accessdate=May 4, 2013|publisher=FestivalMixMilano.com}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=5; style=\"text-align: center; background:#ffffff;\"\n!Year !!Organization !!Award !!Recipient(s) !!Result\n|-\n| rowspan=2|1986||rowspan=2|[[:it:Laceno d'oro|Festival del cinema neorealistico]]<br>(Neorealist Film Festival)||[[:it:Franco Arcalli|Kim Arcalli]] Plaque||[[:it:Gianni Da Campo|Gianni Da Campo]]<br>(Director)||{{won}}\n|-\n| [[:it:Pietro Bianchi (critico cinematografico)|Pietro Bianchi]] Plaque ||Chantal Bergamo & Enzo Porcelli<br>(Producers)||{{won}}\n|}\n\n==Home media==\nSince its original release in 1986, the film has been subtitled in various languages and distributed internationally on VHS and DVD in numerous countries, including Italy (released as ''Il sapore del grano''),<ref name=\"F